race.comment: Couple of these are close to getting off the mark. SCOOBARTIE (3) looks the hardest to beat. Close to a win and returns to the 1200m after finding the five furlongs too sharp latest. Only try at this trip just missed and has good early speed but suspect off the low draw will just stalk the lead throughout. NICALOHA (1) was close to a win before a break with a couple of minors before being safely held at Morphettville last run. Expected to be running on hard here fresh. MADAM MILLY (5) returned from a break over 1100m at Clare and boxed on okay for fourth. Strips fitter and extra trip a plus. Can do much better.  TERMINAL SHOCK (7) is a four start maiden and runs better than they look. Placed in a recent trial and expected to measure up this company.
